<tr>
        <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><a href="download_script.php?src_id=377">EasyHtml.vim</a></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><b>0.2</b></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><i>2001-11-26</i></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap>6.0</td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top"><i><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=355">Gontran BAERTS</a></i></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" width="2000">- Attributs list is now alphabetically sorted<br>- Hitting &lt;F3&gt; allows to display attributs list in Insert mode too<br>- Allows to select an attribut by incremental search :-)<br>For example, with &lt;body&gt; tag, typing &quot;onk&quot; (normal mode) in the attributs list buffer automatically select &quot;onkeydown&quot; attribut. Use backspace (&lt;BS&gt;) to remove characters. This behavior is enable by setting g:eh_incsearch variable to 1. Warning : when incremental attribut search is on, 'q', 'h', 'j', 'k' and 'l' keys aren't used to exit from list and to move highlighting. Use 'Q', '&lt;Left&gt;', '&lt;Down&gt;', '&lt;Up&gt;' and '&lt;Right&gt;' instead.<br>- Check for attributs list already opened, and reuse it</td>
